data.Sentence_cn: 最新消息
data.Sentence: --- lesson 135  The latest report

data.Sentence_cn: 马什小姐，您真的准备退休吗？
data.Sentence: Are you really going to retire, Miss Marsh?

data.Sentence_cn: 有可能退。
data.Sentence: I may.

data.Sentence_cn: 我还拿不定主意。
data.Sentence: I can't make up my mind.

data.Sentence_cn: 我得问一下我的未婚夫。
data.Sentence: I will have to ask my future husband.

data.Sentence_cn: 他不会再让我拍电影了。
data.Sentence: He won't let me make another film.

data.Sentence_cn: 您的未婚夫，马什小姐？
data.Sentence: Your future husband, Miss Marsh?

data.Sentence_cn: 是的，让我把他给你们介绍一下。
data.Sentence: Yes. Let me introduce him to you.

data.Sentence_cn: 他叫卡洛斯。
data.Sentence: His name is Carlos.

data.Sentence_cn: 下星期我们就要结婚了。
data.Sentence: We're going to get married next week.

data.Sentence_cn: 看啊，莉兹！
data.Sentence: Look, Liz!

data.Sentence_cn: 这又有一篇关于卡伦.马什的报道。
data.Sentence: Here's another report about Karen Marsh.

data.Sentence_cn: 你听，“卡伦.马什:最新消息。
data.Sentence: Listen:"Karen Marsh: The latest.

data.Sentence_cn: 今天在伦敦旅馆，马什小姐告诉记者她可能要退休。
data.Sentence: At her London Hotel today Miss Marsh told reporters she might retire.

data.Sentence_cn: 她说她还拿不定主意。
data.Sentence: She said she couldn't make up her mind.

data.Sentence_cn: 她说她得问问她的未婚夫。
data.Sentence: She said she would have to ask her future husband.

data.Sentence_cn: 她说她的未婚夫不会再让她拍电影。
data.Sentence: She said her future husband would not let her make another film.

data.Sentence_cn: 然后她把我们介绍给卡洛斯，并告诉我们说他们下星期结婚。”
data.Sentence: Then she introduced us to Carlos and told us they would get married next week."

data.Sentence_cn: 凯特，这真是条轰动的消息，是不是？
data.Sentence: That's sensational news,isn't it, Kate?

data.Sentence_cn: 当然啦。
data.Sentence: It certainly is.

data.Sentence_cn: 他将是她的第6个丈夫！
data.Sentence: He'll be her sixth husband!
